```

When there's no input (CONTROLLER_INPUT_NONE), I check if `controller->last_valid_sensor_ms > 0`. If it's 0 (no valid sensor at all), I set SAFE_OFF and timed_out = True. But this is wrong - we should only timeout if there's been NO new data for 1000ms, not immediately when there's no input.

The issue is that after boot, `controller->last_valid_sensor_ms = 0`, so the timeout check triggers immediately. But we should wait until enough time has passed before timing out.

